NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
THE MIDWEST; 
</P>
<P>
HEAVY SNOW BLAMED FOR DEATHS IN 4 STATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents in the Midwest were digging out after a deadly blizzard that dumped 
up to two feet of snow. The snowstorm caused at least nine deaths in Wisconsin, 
six in Iowa, one in western Pennsylvania and four in Indiana. At least four 
inches of snow and 25-m.p.h. winds hampered driving in north-central Indiana. 
</P>
