<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAY INCREASES FOR FEDERAL RETIREES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I take exception to Keith's remarks "that the average federal pensioner is 
getting double dips and triple scoops, all of them with COLAs like me." 
</P>
<P>
Very few are getting Social Security. Social Service retirees receive COLAs. 
Why not federal retirees? 
</P>
<P>
I do not believe, however, that all individuals should be eligible for Social 
Security benefits; if they have an income over a certain amount, they should 
not receive Social Security. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN R. RUDDELL 
</P>
<P>
San Pedro 
</P>
</TEXT>
