<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
SHELL HAS NO USE FOR RUN-AND-SHOOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach Art Shell doesn't like the run-and-shoot offense that the Raiders will 
face when they play the Detroit Lions at the Pontiac Silverdome Monday night, 
and he's not sure how to stop it. 
</P>
<P>
"They have a lot of people running all over the place," he said of the Lions. 
</P>
<P>
"They've got four wide receivers running all over the place, and it seems when 
you watch them, somebody's always open. You've got to make sure you confuse the 
quarterback a bit, and always be aware of where Mr. (tailback Barry) Sanders 
is." 
</P>
<P>
Bo Jackson's 117 yards rushing Sunday during the Raiders' 23-20 victory over 
the Broncos in Denver was his first 100-yard effort of the season. . . . With 
his eight-yard sack of the Broncos' John Elway, Greg Townsend has tied his 
career-best sack mark of 11 1/2 in a season. He has four games remaining. 
Townsend finished with 11 1/2 sacks in 1988 and 1986. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
