<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : FATHERS OF SLAIN STUDIO GUARDS SUE NEW 
MEXICO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fathers of two Universal Studios guards killed by a man accused in the 
previous murders of three people in Albuquerque have filed suit against the New 
Mexico state Department of Public Safety and Albuquerque police. 
</P>
<P>
The wrongful death lawsuit was filed in state court in Albuquerque on behalf of 
the fathers of Armando Torres and Jeren Beeks. 
</P>
<P>
The two were shot to death by Nathan Trupp at the movie studio in Universal 
City while New Mexico officials were looking for Trupp in connection with three 
murders at an Albuquerque bagel shop. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit contends that the Albuquerque Police Department, the Public Safety 
Department and their officers failed to share information in a timely fashion, 
which would have led to Trupp's arrest before he left Albuquerque. City Atty. 
David Campbell said his office would mount a vigorous defense. 
</P>
<P>
In May, Trupp, 43, was found not guilty by reason of insanity in the Universal 
Studios slayings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
