COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HOT-SHOOTING SADDLEBACK MEN ROUT GROSSMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saddleback College shot 62% Tuesday night in defeating Grossmont, 98-76, in a 
nonconference men's basketball game at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Thompson led the Gauchos (5-3) with 20 points and Kenny Caesar added 17. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 95, Los Angeles Harbor 29 -- Danielle Silva scored 30 points, 
setting a Saddleback single-game record on 12-of-15 shooting from the field. 
She made six of seven free throws. Kristen Okura added 15 points and nine 
rebounds for Saddleback (6-2). 
</P>
