<P>
LESLIE'S 20 POINTS SPARKS USC VICTORY OVER SAN DIEGO ST. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman Lisa Leslie's 20 points and 23 rebounds led No. 21 USC to a 68-54 
victory over San Diego State Tuesday night at the Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
Leslie's rebounds fell one shy of the USC single-game record, set in 1984 by 
Cheryl Miller. The Trojans outrebounded San Diego State, 65-44. 
</P>
<P>
Coming off its first loss of the season, USC (3-1) held San Diego State 
scoreless through the first 12:11 of the second half, building a 20-point lead. 
Joni Easterly scored three baskets during an 8-0 run to make it 53-33 with 7:49 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
No. 11 Cal State Long Beach 106, Arizona 62 -- Penny Moore scored 22 points and 
grabbed six rebounds to lead Long Beach at University Gym. 
</P>
