<TEXT>
<P>
Child World Posts Loss, May Sell: Child World Inc., the nation's second-largest 
toy supermarket chain, said it may put itself up for sale after reporting a 
substantial third-quarter loss. 
</P>
<P>
The company, whose profit margin is being eroded by intense price competition, 
said it lost $14.4 million in the period. The Avon, Mass. firm lost $4.1 
million in the 1989 period. Third-quarter sales rose 18% to $185.6 million. 
Child World also said it will suspend principal payments to its lenders through 
Jan. 15 to conserve cash. 
</P>
