</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBS Tries to Revise Baseball Pact: CBS Sports, which may have lost up to $100 
million in the first year of its Major League Baseball pact, has asked baseball 
for some of its money back. 
</P>
<P>
CBS Inc. said last month that it expected losses in 1990's fourth quarter, 
largely because of its $1.06-billion, four-year deal, and now the network 
apparently wants Major League Baseball to help share the load. Published 
reports have also said that if baseball is not willing to give CBS a rebate, 
the network wants more games. CBS showed only 16 regular-season games in its 
first year of the deal, while ESPN, which paid baseball $400 million for four 
years, showed 161. 
</P>
