<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No Go for Van Gogh: A Vincent van Gogh painting owned by Elizabeth Taylor 
failed to sell at auction when bidding did not reach the minimum acceptable 
price. 
</P>
<P>
Bidding on "View of the Asylum and Chapel at St. Remy" started at $9.6 million 
and reached $11.14 million, Christie's of London said, but did not achieve the 
undisclosed minimum price. The auction house had expected the painting to fetch 
between $15 million and $19 million. The work depicts the asylum where Van Gogh 
committed himself toward the end of his troubled life. The actress bought it in 
1963 for about $165,000. BETH KLEID 
</P>
