<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
HEALTH PROFESSIONAL ON TOP OF ACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 53-year-old Fullerton man has been selected to head the West Coast branch of 
ACTION, the federal agency that oversees several national volunteer groups. 
</P>
<P>
Fernando Zepeda, a Fullerton resident for six years, is now the associate 
administrator of operations for the Los Angeles County Department of Health 
Services. 
</P>
<P>
He will take over management of the San Francisco office of ACTION at the end 
of December. 
</P>
<P>
Zepeda said Tuesday that he hopes to use his experience with other volunteer 
agencies to continue to spur Americans to become more involved with others. 
</P>
<P>
ACTION is the umbrella organization that oversees the Foster Grandparent 
Program, the Volunteers in Service to America, the Retired Senior Volunteer 
Program and other groups. 
</P>
<P>
Zepeda served 20 years in the Air Force, retiring as a captain. Since then, he 
has worked with a number of health-care agencies, including serving as director 
of the Office of Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism for Los Angeles County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
