<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRANDE GETS OK TO RETURN, BUT IS UNDECIDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CERRITOS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charlie Brande, former Corona del Mar High School girls' and boys' volleyball 
coach, has agreed not to coach in the Southern Section for the 1990-91 school 
year, but is free to return the following season, Southern Section Commissioner 
Stan Thomas said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Brande and Thomas met for 90 minutes Tuesday to discuss alleged violations of 
Southern Section rules by the coach. 
</P>
<P>
Brande was suspended in August in the wake of an investigation into his 
coaching of club team players with high school eligibility remaining. Corona 
del Mar went on to win the Southern Section 5-A and State Division I titles. 
</P>
<P>
Brande said Tuesday he is unsure if he will return to coaching at the high 
school level. 
</P>
<P>
"There's a possibility I could return to Corona del Mar or any other high 
school," Brande said, "or it might be time to move on to coaching a college 
team." 
</P>
<P>
Brande and Thomas also discussed "gray areas" in the eligibility guidelines for 
club coaches who also coach high school teams. Brande, chairman of the ethics 
committee for the U.S Volleyball Assn., said he will distribute clarifications 
of the rules to the club coaches. 
</P>
<P>
"There was a very strong spirit of cooperation with Charlie to work within the 
framework of the rules," Thomas said. "This thing is over. Finally." MIKE 
REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
