<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/ TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comarco's Contracts: But another local company has had somewhat better luck 
landing defense contracts. 
</P>
<P>
Comarco Inc., an Anaheim engineering and computer services company, has been 
awarded four contracts worth more than $12 million. 
</P>
<P>
The contracts are with four different government customers and vary in length 
from 10 months to five years, Comarco President Don M. Bailey said. 
</P>
<P>
The biggest of the contracts is a $5-million award to provide computer software 
support to the U.S. Army. The other contracts involve various services for the 
U.S. Navy, the U.S. Air Force and National Airport in Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
The company also reported that its earnings for the third quarter ended Oct. 21 
rose 53% to $458,000 from $299,000 a year earlier. Sales dropped 11% to $16.4 
million from $18.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
