</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Selling Gradco Shares: About two months after being ousted as chairman of 
Gradco Systems Inc., Keith B. Stewart is selling off a chunk of his stock in 
the Irvine office equipment company. 
</P>
<P>
Stewart, who lost control of Gradco in a proxy contest last October, plans to 
sell 41,098 shares of the company's stock, according to a filing with the 
Securities and Exchange Commission. In September, Stewart owned 725,098 of 
Gradco's 7.6 million common shares, or about 9.5% of the firm. Martin Tash, 
chairman of New York-based Plenum Publishing, gained control of Gradco's board 
in a proxy fight and took over as chairman of the company after Stewart 
resigned. 
