<TEXT>
<P>
Honda Motor Co. Ltd., whose cars have become a hit with U.S. consumers, is 
getting worried about its weak sales in Japan, industry analysts said today. 
</P>
<P>
Sales in Japan in November totaled 32,960 vehicles, down a sharp 27.9% from a 
year earlier and marking the second straight monthly fall. Meanwhile, U.S. 
sales continued to grow strongly, with the Accord remaining the single 
top-selling model for the second year. 
</P>
<P>
The company plans to increase its sales force and the number of its repair 
shops in Japan to counteract its decline, he said. 
