<P>
SEAGRAM NET HITS $189 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seagram Co. Ltd. today reported third-quarter earnings of $189 million, or 
$2.01 a share, up 11% from $170 million, or $1.77 a share, a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenues at the beverage company increased to $1.49 billion from $1.36 billion 
in the third quarter of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
At the end of nine months, Seagram's earnings rose to $581 million, or $6.16 a 
share, from $565 million, or $5.84 a share, in 1989. Revenues increased to 
$4.19 billion from $3.89 billion in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Edgar Bronfman Jr., president and chief operating officer, said the 
third-quarter results reflected a strong performance by the company's 
international division, currency translations, operating income advances with 
the Europe and global markets group divisions and lower orange juice costs. 
</P>
