<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nick Faldo of England, winner of the Masters and British Open, was named PGA 
Player-of-the-Year by the Golf Writers Assn. of America. Lee Trevino, winner of 
seven tournaments, including the U.S. Open, was named Player-of-the-Year on the 
Senior PGA Tour. Beth Daniel, who topped the money-winning list and collected 
seven victories on the LPGA Tour, was named the top LPGA player. 
</P>
